---
title: Hulu’s Secret Chef: Spicy Shrimp Soup with Bok Choy, Scallion Sour Cream & Crispy Fried Onions
description: Inspired by one of the winning dishes on Hulu’s newest reality cooking competition series, Secret Chef, this spicy shrimp soup’s ingredients come together for one unbelievably delicious one-pot meal. You’ll cook scallions, bok choy, and tender napa cabbage in butter along with chopped shrimp to make a savory base. Add spicy-sweet Szechuan paste and tart vinegar to hit all those bold flavor notes. Now here’s the creative part: You’ll top the soup with zippy-cool scallion sour cream and crunchy fried onions. It’s almost like sour cream and onion chips meet hot and sour soup, all in one lucky bowl! Genius, right?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pot-spicy-shrimp-soup-ab8a4422.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6476151d2adaffbd433f7f38.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: Asian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-spicy-shrimp-soup-6476151d2adaffbd433f7f38
course: main course
nutrition:
